      "role": "user",
      "content": "here's the script:\n\n```python\n# deprecate_agents.py\nimport os\nimport shutil\n\ndef remove_agent_runtime():\n    print(\"Starting deprecation of AgentRuntime...\")\n    # Remove core logic and state files\n    if os.path.exists('./core/runtime'):\n        shutil.rmtree('./core/runtime')\n    if os.path.exists('./data/state'):\n        shutil.rmtree('./data/state')\n    print(\"AgentRuntime has been removed. System now operates in stateless mode.\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    remove_agent_runtime()\n```\n\nand here's the main integration test that hits the runtime:\n\n```python\n# tests/integration/test_agent_flow.py\nimport unittest\nfrom core.runtime import AgentRuntime\n\nclass TestAgentFlow(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_continuous_task_execution(self):\n        runtime = AgentRuntime(config=\"default\")\n        result = runtime.run_task(\"analyze logs\")\n        self.assertTrue(result.success)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n```\n\nbasically, once we run the script, the `AgentRuntime` class won't even exist anymore. let me know if you think this will cause a cascade of failures in the repo.",
